oieties of the royal Hastinapura clan triumphs in the end, for it is the Yadava band of Krsna who achieve real victory. That is, it is the matriline and not the patriline that secures ultimate success: it is the kinship group of Krsna-the heroic figure who was to become the dominant Vaisnava icon of classical India-who benefits most from the terrible Bharata war.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 0aKings and rulers in literature. 0aYudhiṣṭhira (Hindu mythology). 4aAsian Studies. 4aFolklore. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Asian / Indic.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Contemporary Collection eBook Packagez978311064982608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCOR eBook Package 2017z978311062534908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCOR eBook-Package Pilot Project 2017z978311066587108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell Univ. Press eBook-Package Pilot Project 2016-2017z978311060673740uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/9781501708220423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781501708220.jpg  a978-3-11-060673-7  Cornell Univ. Press eBook-Package Pilot Project 2016-2017c2016d2017  a978-3-11-062534-9  COR eBook Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-064982-6  Asian Studies Contemporary Collection eBook Package  a978-3-11-066587-1  COR eBook-Package Pilot Project 2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles